                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Catalogue no. 61; Nelson collection no. N355.  Amenothes, son of Psenamounis is Muhs&amp;apos; Taxpayer 27.  1/6 (silver kite) or 2 obols + 1/6 silver (kite) or 2 obols = 1/3 silver (kite) or 4 obols is the price of 1 kotule or 0.27 liter + 1 kotule or 0.27 liter = 2 kotulai or 0.54 liter of oil.  For this writing of the fraction 1/6, see Chauveau, Enchoria 14, p. 26, n. 11,2.  The reading is confirmed here by arithmetic.  The scribe Esminis was responsible for many other price of oil receipts from Thebes between years 30 and 38 of Ptolemy II.  (See additional OIM ostraca.)</note>
